Weather forecasts indicate the cold and wet conditions will persist into Wednesday. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Disaster management personnel in the Western Cape are on high alert after a cold front brought heavy rainfall to the Mother City. Weather forecasts indicate the cold and wet conditions will persist into Wednesday. READ: Authorities on high alert as cold front approaches Western Cape Community leaders in Joe Slovo informal settlement in Langa said they'll be offering alternative accommodation to residents impacted by flooding. * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.